{
  "texts": [
    "Cervical cancer develops in the cervix cells of the uterus's lower part.",
    "Cervical cancer is usually caused by infection with human papillomaviruses (HPV), which is spread through sexual contact.",
    "Cervical cancer is the second largest cause of cancer mortality among women, according to statistics [1].",
    "The majority of the documented cases in 2018 are from poor and developed countries [2].",
    "Cervical cancer accounts for 6.5 per cent of all cancers in women."
  ]
}